description: The Senate voted 50-48 on Saturday to confirm the Supreme Court nomination of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh.
title: How Every Senator Voted on Kavanaugh’s Confirmation
title_page: How Every Senator Voted on Kavanaugh’s Confirmation - The New York Times
maintext: Senator Lisa Murkowski of Alaska announced that she would have voted no, but withdrew her vote as a courtesy to Senator Steve Daines of Montana. Mr. Daines, who would have voted yes, was attending his daughter’s wedding. Senator Joe Manchin III of West Virginia was the only Democrat to vote yes.
